India’s April Oil-Product Sales Climb 2.6% on Higher Growth

-- B y   A r c h a n a   C h a u d h a r y
-- 
2011-06-08T08:55:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-08/india-s-april-oil-product-sales-climb-2-6-on-higher-growth.html
India ’s oil-product sales increased
for the sixth consecutive month in April as the nation’s
manufacturing grew at the fastest pace in five months and
vehicle sales climbed.  Fuel sales climbed 2.6 percent from a year earlier to 14.3
million metric tons, according to preliminary government data.
Diesel, which accounts for about 40 percent of sales, gained 6.6
percent to 5.98 million tons. Gasoline sales climbed 10.8
percent to 1.42 million tons.  India’s exports for the year ended March 31 rose 38 percent
to $245.9 billion, the commerce ministry said on May 2.  Maruti
Suzuki India Ltd. (MSIL) , the country’s largest carmaker, sold 97,155
vehicles in April, a growth of 4.4 percent.  Jet-fuel sales climbed 9.7 percent to 508,070 tons and
liquefied petroleum gas, used as cooking fuel and to power
vehicles, grew 9.1 percent to 1.39 million tons.  Sales of liquefied natural gas fell 2.3 percent to 804,190
tons, while kerosene use declined 4 percent to 892,780. Naphtha,
a chemical feedstock, dropped 0.7 percent to 895,060 tons.  To contact the reporter on this story:
